Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1271
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 16-18-2; IC 16-21-9.5; IC 27-1; IC 27-8-5.7;
IC 27-13-36.2.
Synopsis: Payment of health claims. Requires a hospital to: (1)
disclose information concerning payment assistance programs; (2) post
signs concerning the programs in specified locations of the hospital;
and (3) make information concerning the programs available to
individuals through the hospital's patient portal system. Requires a
hospital to notify individuals of available payment assistance programs
before beginning a collection action against the individual. Requires
the department of insurance to initiate rulemaking to effectuate the
provisions regarding out-of-pocket expense credits not later than July
1, 2026. Prohibits an insurer that issues a policy of accident and
sickness insurance (insurer) and a health maintenance organization
from using downcoding in a specified manner. Prohibits an insurer and
a health maintenance organization from retroactively reducing the
reimbursement rate for any CPT code. Sets forth limitations on an
insurer and a health maintenance organization retroactively auditing a
paid claim or seeking recoupment or a refund of a paid claim.
Effective: Upon passage; July 1, 2026.
McGuire
January 6, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Insurance.
