17 SECTION 4. IC 16-21-9.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
18 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
19 JULY 1, 2026]:
20 Chapter 9.5. Notice of Payment Assistance Programs
21 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "payment assistance program"
22 refers to any of the following:
23 (1) Charity care.
24 (2) Financial assistance.
25 (3) Discounted care.
26 (4) Assistance programs offered as part of a nonprofit
27 hospital's community benefits plan.
28 Sec. 2. (a) A hospital shall provide written notice of the
29 hospital's payment assistance program to a patient or the patient's
30 representative at the following times:
31 (1) During registration or intake for inpatient or outpatient
32 services.
33 (2) At discharge, either in a written format or electronically
34 through a patient portal system.
35 (3) With the initial billing statement for the provided services.
36 (b) The written notice required under subsection (a) must
37 include the following:
38 (1) A description of available payment assistance programs.
39 (2) Eligibility criteria.
40 (3) Application instructions.
41 (4) Contact information for a hospital representative when
42 assistance is needed to complete the application.
2026 IN 1271—LS 7085/DI 141

3
1 (c) A hospital may provide notice to a patient or the patient's
2 representative under subsection (a):
3 (1) in a writing delivered to the patient or the patient's
4 representative;
5 (2) by electronic mail; or
6 (3) through a mobile application or another Internet based
7 method, if available;
8 according to the preference for communication expressed by the
9 patient or patient's representative.
10 Sec. 3. A hospital shall post conspicuous signage notifying
11 patients of the availability of payment assistance programs in the
12 following locations:
13 (1) Inpatient and outpatient registration areas.
14 (2) Financial counseling offices.
15 (3) Emergency departments.
16 The signs must be printed in at least the five (5) most used
17 languages spoken in the county based on the most recent United
18 States Census Bureau American Community Survey.
19 Sec. 4. A hospital shall make payment assistance program
20 information available electronically through any patient portal
21 maintained by the hospital.
22 Sec. 5. Before beginning a collection action, a hospital shall do
23 the following:
24 (1) Determine whether the individual is eligible for a payment
25 assistance program.
26 (2) Make a reasonable effort to notify the individual of
27 available payment assistance programs and provide the
28 individual with an application form.
29 Sec. 6. A nonprofit hospital shall annually report compliance
30 with this chapter as part of the nonprofit hospital's community
31 benefit plan report under IC 16-21-9-7.
32 Sec. 7. The state department may adopt rules under IC 4-22-2
33 to administer and enforce this chapter.
34 Sec. 8. The state department may assess a hospital a civil
35 penalty of not more than one thousand dollars ($1,000) per
36 violation for failure to comply with this chapter. A penalty
37 collected under this section shall be deposited into the state general
38 fund.
