3 SECTION 6. IC 27-1-52 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE AS
4 A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
5 1, 2026]:
6 Chapter 52. Downcoding of Health Benefits Claims
7 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "covered individual" means an
8 individual who is entitled to coverage under a health plan.
9 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "downcoding" means the
10 adjustment of a health benefits claim by an insurer to a less
11 complex or lower price service for reimbursement to a provider in
12 an amount less than the amount noted in the fully executed
13 provider contract. The term includes the use of remittance advice
14 remark codes.
15 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "health benefits claim" means a
16 claim submitted by a provider for payment under a health plan for
17 health care services provided to a covered individual.
18 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "health care service" means a
19 service or good furnished for the purpose of preventing,
20 alleviating, curing, or healing:
21 (1) human illness;
22 (2) physical disability; or
23 (3) injury.
24 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "health plan" means the
25 following:
26 (1) A policy of accident and sickness insurance (as defined in
27 IC 27-8-5-1), but not including the coverages described in
28 IC 27-8-5-2.5(a).
29 (2) An individual contract (as defined in IC 27-13-1-21) or a
30 group contract (as defined in IC 27-13-1-16) with a health
31 maintenance organization (as defined in IC 27-13-1-19) that
32 provides coverage for basic health care services (as defined in
33 IC 27-13-1-4).
34 Sec. 6. As used in this chapter, "insurer" means the following:
35 (1) An insurer (as defined in IC 27-1-2-3(x)) that issues a
36 policy of accident and sickness insurance (as defined in
37 IC 27-8-5-1), but not including the coverages described in
38 IC 27-8-5-2.5(a).
39 (2) A health maintenance organization (as defined in
40 IC 27-13-1-19) that provides coverage for basic health care
41 services (as defined in IC 27-13-1-4) under an individual
42 contract (as defined in IC 27-13-1-21) or a group contract (as
2026 IN 1271—LS 7085/DI 141

5
1 defined in IC 27-13-1-16).
2 Sec. 7. As used in this chapter, "provider" means an individual
3 or entity licensed or legally authorized to provide health care
4 services.
5 Sec. 8. Notwithstanding any other law or regulation to the
6 contrary, an insurer may not use downcoding in a manner that
7 prevents a provider from:
8 (1) submitting a health benefits claim for the actual health
9 care service performed; and
10 (2) collecting reimbursement from the insurer for the actual
11 health care service performed.
12 Sec. 9. The department shall adopt rules under IC 4-22-2 to
13 carry out this chapter.
