8 SECTION 11. IC 27-8-5.7-9.7 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
9 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
10 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 9.7. (a) Subject to section 10 of
11 this chapter, an insurer may not seek recoupment or a refund of a
12 payment made to a health provider facility that provided initial
13 health care services to an individual who was subsequently
14 transferred to another health provider facility unless:
15 (1) the insurer determines that the claim was submitted
16 fraudulently; or
17 (2) the:
18 (A) individual was not entitled to coverage; or
19 (B) health care services provided to the individual were not
20 covered;
21 at the time the health care services were rendered.
22 (b) The limitation on seeking recoupment or refund of a
23 payment made to a health provider facility under subsection (a)
24 applies regardless of:
25 (1) the reason for the transfer;
26 (2) the type of facility receiving the individual; or
27 (3) the acuity, age, or diagnosis of the individual.
28 (c) Any recoupment or refund attempted in violation of this
29 section is void and unenforceable.
